My Grandfather used to say “You gotta know where you came from before you can know where your going.” #wiseoldblkman
Theory of Flight as Discussed by a Millenial
“Have You Heard?” (A Man was Lynched Yesterday)

This Friday, 12/15 at 10am PST we are releasing “Finally Some Alone Time” only on www.hebrubrantley.com/hebrubrandstore. This print  is a 32 x 29” digital print with a regular edition of 155. 

“Finally Some Alone Time” is a narrative on traveling without moving and is approached in multiple ways - the meditative state in which one becomes enlightened, how music travels sonically, or the manner in which relationships facilitate individual and collective thought. Though movement can lead to growth, speed and distance are abstract concepts when it comes to reaching maturity. The inherent growth is in the process of understanding where one came from and through this, where one needs to go.
